## 6. Evaluation

### 6.1 Feature Comparison

| Feature | .wia | Jupyter | RUNME | Org-mode | Ansible |
|---------|:----:|:-------:|:-----:|:--------:|:-------:|
| Shell execution | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
| SQL execution | ✓ | ~ | ✗ | ✓ | ~ |
| AI model invocation | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ |
| Verification assertions | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ~ |
| Typed inputs | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ |
| Secret masking | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ |
| Approval gates | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ~ |
| Conditional execution | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ | ✓ |
| Rollback/compensation | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ |
| Idempotency | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ |
| Watch/monitoring | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ |
| Compliance logging | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ~ |
| 254-language i18n | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ |
| Plain text / git-friendly | ✓ | ✗ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |

### 6.2 Format Compatibility

Every `.md` file is a valid `.wia` file. Renaming `README.md` to `README.wia` produces a Level 0 conformant document.

### 6.3 Conversion Coverage

30+ input formats supported: `.sh`, `.py`, `.sql`, `.tf`, `.yml`, `.ipynb`, `.json`, `.go`, `.rs`, `.java`, `.rb`, `.lua`, `.proto`, `.graphql`, `.ps1`, `.env`.

### 6.4 Internationalization

254 languages via BCP-47 locale tags, covering ~99.7% of the world's population by primary language.

